We recommend that the Local Chief Executive:
To require the contractor and the Municipal Engineer to submit a written explanation/justification for the delays incurred in the completion of the Phase I project; 
To require the immediate completion of the project (Phase I) to facilitate the implementation of the Phase II;
To impose liquidated damages on the contractor equal to at least one tenth (1/10) of one percent of the cost of the unperformed portion of works for every day of delay pursuant to Item 8.1 of Annex “E” of the 2016 Revised IRR of RA No. 9184; and
To adopt measures and strategies to fast track the implementation of projects.

We recommend that management to:

Require the concerned officers and employee to immediately settle the unpaid loan amortizations; 
Strictly enforce the deduction/withholding of the required loan amortization from the monthly payroll of the employee;
Require the OIC-Municipal Treasurer to remit the withheld monthly amortizations to the GSIS on time to avoid the imposition of penalty/ies;
Require the AAO and ERF Officer to act prudently in approving the loans of GSIS member-employees.

We recommended that the LCE require the OIC-Municipal Accountant to review all the JEV and the posting in the subsidiary ledger/schedule of the PPE items of respective PPE accounts and prepare the necessary adjusting JEV to correct the deficiencies noted above to have a fair presentation of the accounts in the financial statements;
Moving forward, we recommended that the LCE; (a) require the Municipal Accounting Office to maintain a separate subsidiary ledger for each project; and (b) require the MEO to maintain the project cost sheet for each project;
Moreover, we recommended that the OIC-Municipal Accountant to: (a) establish mechanism to ensure that the entries in the books of accounts of the municipality are actual transactions and/or are based on the actual transactions consummated/incurred during the period; and (b) ensure compliance with the IPSAS 17 on accounting and reporting of the PPE.

